    <briefdescription>
<para>The class <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1Delaunay__mesh__size__criteria__2" kindref="compound">Delaunay_mesh_size_criteria_2</ref></computeroutput> is a model for the <computeroutput><ref refid="classMeshingCriteria__2" kindref="compound">MeshingCriteria_2</ref></computeroutput> concept. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The shape criterion on triangles is given by a bound <formula id="0">$ B$</formula> such that for good triangles <formula id="1">$ \frac{r}{l} \le B$</formula> where <formula id="2">$ l$</formula> is the shortest edge length and <formula id="3">$ r$</formula> is the circumradius of the triangle. By default, <formula id="4">$ B=\sqrt{2}$</formula>, which is the best bound one can use with the guarantee that the refinement algorithm will terminate. The upper bound <formula id="0">$ B$</formula> is related to a lower bound <formula id="5">$ \alpha_{min}$</formula> on the minimum angle in the triangle: <formula id="6">\[ \sin{ \alpha_{min} } = \frac{1}{2 B} \]</formula> so <formula id="4">$ B=\sqrt{2}$</formula> corresponds to <formula id="7">$ \alpha_{min} \ge 20.7$</formula> degrees.</para><para>This traits class defines also a size criteria: all segments of all triangles must be shorter than a bound <formula id="9">$ S$</formula>.</para><para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>CDT</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>must be a 2D constrained Delaunay triangulation.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
